  "prompt": "If you had 3 years to live and $3 billion to spend, what would you do?",
  "response": "If I had 3 years to live and $3 billion to spend, I would focus on making a lasting impact on the world and ensuring that my remaining time was meaningful and fulfilling. Here are several steps I might take:\n\n1. **Philanthropy and Social Impact**:\n    - **Medical Research**: Invest in research for diseases that are currently incurable or have limited treatment options. Focus on funding innovative projects and supporting scientists working on breakthrough treatments.\n    - **Education**: Establish scholarships and fund educational institutions in underserved areas to provide quality education and opportunities for students who might not otherwise have access.\n    - **Environment**: Support initiatives aimed at addressing climate change, conservation efforts, and sustainable development projects.\n    - **Social Justice**: Provide grants to organizations working on human rights, gender equality, and social justice issues.\n\n2. **Personal Legacy**:\n    - **Create Foundations**: Set up foundations that will continue to support various causes after I am gone, ensuring that the impact of my contributions lasts beyond my lifetime.\n    - **Art and Culture**: Fund cultural projects such as museums, galleries, and art programs to preserve and promote the arts.\n\n3. **Experiences and Relationships**:\n    - **Travel**: Visit places I have always wanted to see, experiencing different cultures and learning from diverse perspectives. Make sure to travel with loved ones to create lasting memories.\n    - **Quality Time**: Spend meaningful time with family and friends, building deeper connections and cherishing the moments together.\n\n4. **Personal Fulfillment**:\n    - **Pursue Passions**: Engage in hobbies and interests that bring joy and fulfillment, whether it\u2019s writing, painting, playing music, or other creative pursuits.\n    - **Health and Well-being**: Focus on maintaining a healthy lifestyle to maximize the quality of the remaining years.\n\n5. **Community Building**:\n    - **Support Local Initiatives**: Invest in local community projects and businesses that create jobs and improve the quality of life for residents.\n    - **Mentorship**: Mentor young entrepreneurs and leaders, sharing knowledge and experiences to help them succeed.\n\nUltimately, I would aim to use the resources at my disposal to leave the world a better place, create lasting memories with loved ones, and ensure that my contributions continue to make a positive impact long after I am gone.",
